    MOD 1 - NEW EVALUATION OF n + 240U REACTIONS                  9243 1451
 P.G. Young, M.B. Chadwick, R.E. MacFarlane, P. Taloe, T. Kawano  9243 1451
                   September 18, 2003                             9243 1451
                                                                  9243 1451
                         SUMMARY                                  9243 1451
                                                                  9243 1451
  A new evaluation of n + 240U reactions has been completed       9243 1451
covering the energy range from 1.0e-5 eV to 30 MeV.  The          9243 1451
evaluation is based on theoretical optical model and Hauser-      9243 1451
Feshbach-preequilibrium model calculations over the energy range  9243 1451
10 keV to 30 MeV.  Below 10 keV a resonance parameter             9243 1451
representation from a neighboring nucleus is adapted for the 240U 9243 1451
evaluation.                                                       9243 1451
                                                                  9243 1451
****************************************************************  9243 1451
                                                                  9243 1451
                  THEORETICAL ANALYSIS                            9243 1451
                                                                  9243 1451
   To provide the new data, coupled channel optical model calcu-  9243 1451
lations were performed with the ECIS96 code for the lowest 5      9243 1451
members of the U240 ground state rotational band. The optical     9243 1451
model potential (Yo92) used in these calculations is available    9243 1451
from the RIPL-2 OMP library as RIPL-2 potential number 5.  The    9243 1451
calculations were used to provide elastic and inelastic cross     9243 1451
sections and angular distributions for discrete states of 240U,   9243 1451
as well as the neutron total cross section.  Similar calculations 9243 1451
coupling 3 states were used to provide neutron transmission       9243 1451
coefficients for nuclear reaction theory calculations with the    9243 1451
GNASH (Ch01,Yo98) Hauser-Feshbach statistical-preequilibrium      9243 1451
theory code. Fission barrier parameters for the GNASH             9243 1451
calculations were obtained from a systematic analysis (Yo98) of   9243 1451
all the U isotopes that have experimental data.                   9243 1451
  The ECIS96 calculations were used directly in the evaluation    9243 1451
for the neutron total and (n,n') cross sections to the first 4    9243 1451
excited states (MT=51-54) of 240U.  The GNASH calculations were   9243 1451
used for the (n,n') cross sections for MT=55-71 (up to Ex= 1.1    9243 1451
MeV), primarily because they include a small preequilibrium       9243 1451
component that approximates direct reaction effects. For          9243 1451
excitation energies between 1.1 and 3.5 MeV (MT=72-90), cross     9243 1451
sections calculated with ECIS96 for grouped 2+ and 3- vibrational 9243 1451
levels, taken from our 238U evaluation (Yo03), were used to       9243 1451
supplement the continuum cross section.                           9243 1451
  The ECIS96 calculations were used for all elastic and discrete  9243 1451
level angular distributions.  The GNASH calculations were used    9243 1451
for the radiative capture, (n,n'continuum), (n,2n), (n,3n),       9243 1451
(n,4n) and fission cross sections, including first-, second-,     9243 1451
third- and fourth-chance fission.  The GNASH calculations were    9243 1451
also used for the MF=6 energy-angle continuum distributions for   9243 1451
the (n,n'continuum), (n,2n), (n,3n), (n,4n) reactions.            9243 1451
  The (n,gamma) cross section calculation with GNASH requires an  9243 1451
inputted value of 2 pi gamma-gamma/Do, where gamma-gamma is the   9243 1451
average gamma-ray width and Do is the mean level spacing for s-   9243 1451
wave levels.  We chose values of gamma-gamma = 23.2 keV, based on 9243 1451
the 238U value, and Do = 36.66 eV, which is the value obtained    9243 1451
from the default Gilbert and Cameron level density parameters,    9243 1451
reduced by 20%.  This reduction in the default value of Do, which 9243 1451
is well within the uncertainty range, was made in order for the   9243 1451
(n,gamma) cross section to be more consistent with the value at   9243 1451
10 keV from the unresolved resonance parameters.  In spite of     9243 1451
this, it was necessary to reduce gamma-gamma in the unresolved    9243 1451
resonance parameter evaluation for consistency with the smooth    9243 1451
value at 10 keV.                                                  9243 1451
  The 240U(n,f) and 240U(n,gamma) cross sections appear to be     9243 1451
consistent at most important energies with the trends in these    9243 1451
cross sections for 234U, 236U, and 238U reactions.                9243 1451
